The paper deals with Bayesian auctions, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the analysis of distributions and their impact on auction mechanisms, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses mathematical techniques to derive bounds on expected revenue, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or information theory (cs.IT).
